A cozy home study corner in warm afternoon light, featuring a beautifully crafted wall-mounted desk made of layered hardwood plywood with visible edge grain showing multiple golden-brown laminations. The desk surface is clean and minimalist with a simple potted succulent and a closed notebook. Soft shadows fall across the wood grain, highlighting the natural texture and waxed finish. The wall behind shows subtle texture, and a comfortable modern chair is partially visible. Shot in photorealistic style with shallow depth of field focusing on the elegant rounded edge detail of the plywood, emphasizing craftsmanship and the satisfaction of a DIY woodworking project coming to life.
